      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MORNING DAYLIGHT (5) is a super honest type rarely out of the placings, including wins at her last four on end, the latest at Gosford (22.08). Solid record at the distance winning three races. Looks the testing material here. IBROX MAVERICK (1) has a strong winning strike-rate over this track and trip with four wins and a placing from eight tries. Recorded a 0.8 lengths win (22.47) in a Grade 5 last time at Gosford. Looks a key chance on best figures. PIRATE RIOT (8) boasts a strong record this journey here with six wins and five minors from 14 tries. Placed last time (25.19) at Maitland in a Grade 5, finishing second and beaten 1.3 lengths. Can feature in the finish. HI LO RAIN (7) made it two minor placings on the trot when beaten third (30.38) in a Grade 5 at this track last time out. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from on outside draw.",
